A certificate that I think is very meaningful.
One of my important skill certificates besides driving license!
First aid is the treatment given to a person who has been injured or become ill suddenly, before a doctor can examine him.
As we all know, there is a certain time period between the accident and the arrival of the ambulance. And this period is crucial.
This is the time for first aid.
If I really have a heart attack, a stroke or a cardiac arrest, then we only have four minutes, the golden four minutes!
It's so important for people around you to know first aid!
When someone is falling down around us, we can learn how to help them instead of standing there frozen and unable to do anything. That feeling of powerlessness is so scary.
In China, there are 3 million accidental deaths per year, with sudden cardiac arrest being the most dangerous.
In the United States, an average of 15 percent of patients were revived.
This is what Lu Le, founder of First Response, said.
If a person has had a cardiac arrest and is not breathing and has no heartbeat, pinching the philtrum will do nothing.
Only by doing artificial respiration and chest compressions can a man be saved.
I found that we are still not aware of first aid, but when it happens, it's too late, so I urge everyone to learn this skill so that we can respond in time when faced with emergencies.
may even save a life!
You can sign up for a first aid certificate at your local Red Cross training center, I got the certificate from the Red Cross training center in Zhuhai, there are discounts for students.
PS: Last picture is my goal list before I turned 25, adding the first aid certificate to it was also a few months ago, but I really finished it!
Then I have to go for other certificates, plan to get a diving certificate, before on REDnote saw that there is also a diving first aid certificate, it seems that I need to have a first aid certificate to get this one, so actually the first aid certificate is very useful!
