The Beijing Municipal Education Commission announced yesterday that it will implement a new training model of "modern apprenticeship" in 60 secondary vocational schools. Students admitted to the schools will be pre-recruited as unit employees by the pilot enterprises.
Pilot schools must reform talent training model.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training programs, formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality monitoring standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The training period is determined according to the professional talent training plan, and the internship is generally six months.
In enterprise practice, enterprise team management model should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, one master can take 2-5 apprentices to form a learning group to ensure that students master the skills required for each rotation post.
According to the plan, from 2016 to August 2019, our city will determine 60 pilot schools for modern apprenticeship system in municipal secondary vocational schools in three batches. The number of students (apprentices) trained in each school is about 3000.
Explore the establishment of long-term mechanism of joint enrollment, joint training and integrated education between schools and enterprises, improve students' post skills, and increase students' employment rate and quality.
