China's public security ministry has launched a new website to help search for abducted children.
This is an Internet information platform to establish an authoritative channel for missing children's information release and find abducted children in time.
I heard that the name of this App is Reunion, which makes me feel warm.
The new technology is not only artistic and full of emotion, but also properly applied with information technology, practical and effective.
The primary goal of anti-abduction law enforcement is to find abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The trial and punishment of a suspect come next.
The significance of criminal punishment, ranging from individual punishment to social prevention and legal education, can be listed in many long words.
But until the trafficking case is solved, the victim's safety should be a priority.
The priority is to save children trapped in trafficking networks from immediate harm, not to debate the merits of criminal policy proposals which may or may not be more effective in doing so.
In such cases, the traffickers tend to move away from the scene as soon as possible.
Every minute that a missing child is delayed in being reported to the police, the chances of finding her alive and free decrease and the difficulty of solving the case increases.
In this case, to come up with an effective way like the Reunion platform that can help solve the case and find the child back is really a practical action.
After all, "fighting against abduction" is a big task that requires the whole legal system to work well.
Crime fighting, children and parents' rights protection,from legislation improvement, to judicial guarantee, to law enforcement, all need to implement "care for the young and weak".
In addition, prevention of child trafficking can be improved from the family to society.
For example, a common case: a family of three is resting at the railway station. The parents are fast asleep, but when they wake up, their child is gone.
You can't expect a two year old to have adequate self protective skills, but as the parent of a toddler you should at least have reasonable protective awareness.
The simplest steps to prevent a child from being abducted are for parents to take turns resting or leave their children under secure protection.
From another aspect of the police's fight against trafficking in human beings, the buyers of abducted children should also be brought under control and punished.
An isolated aberration is often only a link in a long chain.
According to China's criminal law, the penalty for child trafficking starts with five years in prison; in cases of especially serious circumstances, the death penalty and confiscation of property may be imposed.
The crime of abducting and selling children is obviously a heavy punishment under the trend of "light punishment".
But there are still many cases of trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concept and weak legal awareness in raising children.
Synchronized legal education for this group should follow.
Strict official enforcement is not enough to control trafficking.
Therefore, to break away with backward ideas and popularize legal knowledge can also help to eradicate the crime of abducting and buying children.
