A while back, there was an article called "Look! Project Managers can compete in Olympic events". It mentioned that project managers are definitely the best in many projects: they do everything from brick-carrying to business-trips and staying-up-late. They can also do fire-slowing and even take the blame.
The article seems to be joking, but it also tells us the daily bitterness of project managers, which means they are powerless in current project management work.
Project managers are increasingly choosing action to escape their jobs.
The increasing number of PMP applicants each year shows that more and more project management practitioners are learning to improve their skills.
The number of PMP certification holders has been increasing year by year in the past 10 years, which indicates that more and more project managers realize that relying on simple past “old experience” is not advisable. The ever-changing working environment makes us know that we should learn from scientific giants to explore the way forward.
However, does getting the PMP certification guarantee that project management will go smoothly?
Many beginners in project management said that they have mastered the knowledge of ten knowledge areas and five process groups through learning PMP/IPMP courses, but they still feel confused when actually managing projects.
Many project managers often feedback the following problems: lack of project management awareness, rely on personal experience, have empty project management theory but don't know how to practice; lack of systematic project management process support, can't implement it in work, inaccurate project estimation, poor control sensitivity, project is postponed again and again; unclear member division of labor, "veterans" in the team don't know how to deal with it, cross-departmental assistance communication is not smooth, project is difficult to promote...
Therefore, Zhongtian Huaxia Consulting, which has been focusing on product innovation and R & D management for more than ten years, has helped many excellent enterprises train a large number of key R & D talents such as product managers and project managers, and has won honorary titles such as "China's corporate R & D management training demonstration base". Now it brings you the online course of "R & D Project Management Training Camp".
The Project Management Training Camp is a kind of online fragmented learning, which combines the practical cases, tools and methods of many R & D enterprises to help you master the necessary knowledge and standard actions of project manager and go on your own project management advanced path.
It is also an opportunity for organizations to increase their project management capability with less investment at a lower cost.
Let's take a look at what other students have to say about this course. The course is taught by Zhongtian Huaxia, which consists of former Huawei R & D management team members who combine international advanced project management methodologies and real business scenarios of many well-known enterprises to give a professional explanation of the course content in simple terms.
It will also provide scientific and practical management tools and methods, as well as rich template forms to help students apply what they have learned to their work after class.
