The so-called university spirit refers to a series of school-running concepts and value pursuits formed by a university in the long process of development, which is the soul of a university.
The spirit of university has been vital to the development of politics, economics, culture, technology, society and even a nation.
Since the birth of the world's first modern university, universities have taken on a unique mission different from other social organizations. For Chinese universities, which emerged in times of national crisis, their spirit has been deeply influenced by traditional culture and changes of the times, advocating the value concept of "cultivating virtue for the benefit of the world, regulating oneself and governing the country" and the patriotic responsibility of "revitalizing learning to strengthen the country".
At present, the trend of informatization and internationalization of higher education is becoming increasingly obvious. With the intensification of global educational competition, scientific and technological competition and talent competition, as an important "supply side", the structural reform of higher education is facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges.
The overall plan for world-class universities and disciplines, especially the overall plan for world-class universities and disciplines, demonstrates China's confidence and determination to move from a large-scale higher education country to a strong one.
It is particularly important to realize that there can be no one-size-fits-all world-class universities. Each must show its individuality and distinctive strengths.
School-running characteristics should not only have Chinese characteristics, but also reflect their own unique target positioning, school-running traditions and resource endowments.
In this process it is particularly important to keep the university spirit alive and in tune with the spirit of the times.
For Zhejiang University, the school motto is "Seek truth and innovate", the common values are "Diligence in study, cultivation of virtue, discrimination and truthfulness", and the common spirit is "encompass rivers and seas, enlighten the truth and virtue, open up the world for the people, establish our country".
This is an important guarantee for the school to adhere to the correct direction, continuously accumulate cultural height and gather spiritual strength. It is rich in connotation and far-reaching significance.
This series of spiritual concepts and value pursuits is the soul of Zhejiang University's 120-year history.
The wise hear the word before it is spoken; the intelligent see the form before it is made.
Chinese universities should further base themselves on the overall situation of socialism with Chinese characteristics, grasp the times and historical missions of higher education, and accelerate the construction of world-class universities.
