As NFTs gain traction, a new concept has emerged in the crypto community.
In 2021, a blockchain game called Axie Infinity became a sensation in Southeast Asia, where some residents lost their jobs due to the pandemic and began earning steady incomes from playing.
Axie Infinity is a blockchain-based pet raising game with various gameplay, including NFT. It is the highest trading NFT project, which has exceeded $3 billion as of now.
TokenTerminal data shows that Axie Infinity's daily income is more than $8.2 million, approaching that of Honor of Kings.
On Aug. 6, Axie Infinity announced that its daily active users exceeded 1 million.
The popularity of Axie Infinity spreads a new "play to earn" model. With the help of blockchain and smart contract, players are no longer single characters. They can not only enjoy the game and get economic benefits, but also participate in the governance of the game ecosystem.
This authority is not granted by the game publisher, but assured by blockchain technology.
