How do you drink red label whisky?
Everyone has a different hobby. Some like collecting, some like food, and of course some like wine tasting. Red Label is one of the best selling Scotch Whiskies in various countries at the moment, and Red Label has won the gold medal at the International Spirits Competition.
Every bottle of Red Label has a distinctive taste, but if you don't know how to savour it, you are just destroying its aromas.
So how do you drink Red Label?
The editor will introduce it to you briefly.
How to drink Red Label:
Johnnie Walker Red Label is a blend of approximately 35 single malts from Scotland. It has the rich aromas, sweetness and smokiness that are characteristic of traditional Scotch whisky.
This is a rich, fresh entry with hints of vanilla and smoky malts.
The wine can be enjoyed on the rocks or mixed with your favorite drink.
Red brand is entering domestic market. In order to adapt to the taste of Chinese people, red brand + cola or sprite or new cherry etc bubble drinks become a kind of lasting fashion.
These sweet drinks can neutralize the sourness and visually delight the palate, helping to dilute the wine and change its texture.
The classic cocktail is made with Red Label, sliced lemons and a lump of sugar.
The authentic red square wine has a tart taste, adding sugar can neutralize the acidity, while lemon will bring a fresh fragrance to the wine. Of course, sweet and sour can be adjusted according to personal taste.
The above three ways are the best ways to drink red label whisky, you can try them. I hope my introduction can help you.
Education: How to make the best and the worst students feel equal in college exams?
Three students from Lanzhou Jiaotong University have written to the school leaders, expressing their confusion about the exams and asking for more challenging questions that can truly reflect students' abilities.
Indeed, for a long time, college entrance examinations have been a hot topic.
On a college campus students come from all over the country, with varying abilities and degrees of learning.
Different feelings are inevitable when assessing such a diverse group.
Of course, if the exam papers are too simple and repetitive, it will create a different kind of feeling.
A lazy student may pass an exam by cramming, but a diligent student will achieve twice the result with half the effort.
In this way, there is a strange situation that "underachievers" can get high scores without much effort, while "top students" don't miss any lessons, do their homework and take notes well, but still don't get much higher scores in exams.
It seems that the students of Lanzhou Jiaotong University have a valid reason to complain about the exams. I believe this situation exists not only in Lanzhou Jiaotong University.
In this sense, I want to give a thumbs up to these three students who wrote the letter directly.
In fact, those who have been to college know that cramming for exams, trying every means to get the exam questions from teachers, asking for key points of the exam, and even cheating are not uncommon.
In the author's opinion, as a guide to the quality of teaching, measuring whether or not a university exam is adequate depends more on the teacher's overall grasp of teaching and learning and scientific proposition.
When I enter the undergraduate stage, my major begins to be specialized. Many of my courses are about basic knowledge.
Undoubtedly, whether one has a thorough knowledge of the basic knowledge of a subject is what university exams are all about.
The knowledge in undergraduate is basically basic theory and common sense of the discipline. There is not much room for change. It's basically fixed.
As the teacher said, "I still learn the basic knowledge of college mathematics 20 years ago. It's still the key point."
But the fact that knowledge points remain the same doesn't mean exam questions are repetitive.
In many universities, exams are prepared by panels of teachers who design the questions and papers are coordinated by senior members of the subject. Marking is also done by the whole team of teachers, which helps to prevent repetition.
To design a set of test questions that conform to the reality of teaching and learning, it is necessary to comprehensively master the teaching situation and analyze the degree of students' learning so as to dynamically control the difficulty and types of questions in the examination, highlight the inspection of basic knowledge, take into account the inspection of ability, and innovate the question types.
Examination is the baton of university education. What kind of examination there are, students will have corresponding preparation plans. In the long run, it will affect the effectiveness of university education.
Lanzhou Jiaotong University has taken measures to improve the students' recommendation letters.
All teaching units are required to organize teachers to carry out self-examination and control of the final exam, formulate examination papers and related systems, strengthen the supervision and inspection of the proposition and review of examination papers, refine the evaluation of grades, and strengthen the comprehensive assessment of all aspects of curriculum teaching.
