On the 21st and 22nd, the junior high school entrance examination for special students was organized and implemented by the district education commission.
This year, special students are recruited in a more competitive way in Beijing.
In Dongcheng District, for example, the proportion of students with special skills admitted to junior high school this year will not exceed 5% of the district's enrollment plan, with a planned enrollment of 380 people. The proportion of students admitted to schools will not exceed 10% of the school's enrollment plan.
Students with sports, artistic or technological skills who register online are eligible to be considered for special talent admissions.
To facilitate students to take the exam nearby, Dongcheng District continues last year's arrangement method to set up 1-2 examination sites in each school district, a total of 13 examination sites.
The examination center is divided into examination areas according to the region, and time periods are set up by hour. Students will go to the examination area on the day of the exam according to their assigned time period to take the exam.
On May 23, the district education enrollment and examination center publicized online the list of students who passed the examination. Students can check their examination results online.
