Read the following article, it talks about why this client wants a company inside the bonded area to do canning, although canning is a deep processing and not within the scope of business of a bonded logistics company.
I have been to many milk powder manufacturers and seen many production lines.
The raw materials of canned milk powder and powdered milk in bags are exactly the same. There is no difference at all.
So everybody must be wondering: why is the shelf life of the canned coffee two years or more, while the package is one year?
Or another question:Why is the price difference between canned and bagged so big?
In fact, many consumers or moms think that the reason is that the raw materials are different and the quality is better.
Actually, the raw materials are the same, but people think that expensive is good.
Some consumers even said that the canned taste was different from the fresh one.
Now I will tell you the reason why the tickets are expensive.
Why do they vary so much in price though their raw materials are similar?
When manufacturers set prices, they often take into account that if the price for a bag of chips is too high, consumers will not buy it. That means the manufacturer will make little or no profit. So what keeps manufacturers in business?
So they have a big price increase on the overpriced product to protect their profit margins.
It is therefore the canned rather than the bagged product which is advertised by most manufacturers.
There are also thousands of manufacturers, each paying tens or hundreds of millions of yuan per year for advertising. Where does the money come from?
You can imagine.
With the development of society, marketing costs, such as mall promoters, mall display fees, product premiums, advertising costs, etc. are also increasing.
So all the manufacturers are constantly adding new products, and canned beer is also increasing in price, which is due to the increase in market costs.
The main purpose is to make more profits. In fact, the raw materials cost will not exceed 3 or 4 yuan.
Some brands, in order to promote their products, use all kinds of means to link up with doctors in hospitals. They offer doctors a part of the profits from selling products, ranging from 30 yuan to 80 yuan per bottle.
But Chinese law absolutely forbids such practice, which is actually harmful to consumers.
I suggest that if you have the space to store canned milk powder, buy the powdered milk in bags and put them into the cans. It will save money, increase the storage time of milk powder and keep the cans sealed, and it has no effect on your baby.
Also don't think that the shelf life of canned food is longer than that of bagged food. If the shelf life of both is the same after opening, it's just that bagged food is not easy to preserve and will get damp and deteriorate.
The food is cold, dry and hard, totally impossible to eat!
