The naked carp in Qinghai Lake, commonly known as "Huangyu", is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake. It plays a vital role in maintaining the safety of "water-fish-bird" ecological chain and biodiversity in the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to factors such as massive human hunting and the degradation of the breeding environment of naked fish, the number of naked fish in Qinghai Lake has decreased sharply. In 2002, the resource reserve of naked fish in Qinghai Lake was only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake Gymnothorax was listed as an endangered species in the Chinese Catalog of Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented the policy of closing lakes to fishery development. No unit, collective or individual is allowed to catch Gymnocypris przewalskii in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, nor to sell this fish and its products.
Meanwhile, the resource reserve of Gymnocypris przewalskii is increasing year by year in Qinghai Lake through artificial propagation and stocking as well as cleaning up the river channels of major inflow rivers and designing scientific and reasonable fish passages.
According to Yang Lin, deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, nearly 180 million fish have been released into Qinghai Lake, contributing over 23 percent to the restoration of the species' population.
Sanjiangyuan is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area to control the desertification from spreading eastward.
To protect the ecological environment of Sanjiangyuan region and Qinghai Lake waters, protect aquatic wild animals, maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, since this year, Qinghai has successively issued fishing bans on key waters of the Yangtze River, Yellow River, Qinghai Lake, constructing a comprehensive fishing management system of "one river and one lake".
