Give me some knowledge about male.
Most girls experience their first menstrual period some day between the ages of 13 and 15, and menopause occurs around age 50.
After that, once a month on condition of good health.
But it's not regular enough to predict accurately. It's about one week. I need to prepare in advance, but sometimes bad luck will cause the postponement for several days suddenly.
The length of time, blood loss and degree of pain vary from person to person. Some people will have it for three days, some for a week; some have little bleeding, some have heavy bleeding; some have no reaction, some are so painful that they need ambulance to take them away. Menstrual pain changes over time, not having pain before doesn't mean you won't have it forever.
Uncontrolled menstruation, bleeding 24 hours a day for days at a time until it stops.
Dysmenorrhea is mainly caused by prostaglandin secretion. Take ibuprofen when it starts, it can relieve pain for that month. No use after it begins.
Menstruation causes diarrhea due to blood-accumulation in the uterus and excessive release of prostaglandins.
I have diarrhea for no reason. I will get my period in two days.
It is best to change the sanitary napkin every two or three hours, otherwise bacteria will grow very fast, in the worst case I have to change it 6 times a day, seven days a month, that's 42 pads used, plus one more for backup, making 50 pads used per month.
(Change the sanitary pad not frequently, about five or six hours, at most eight hours)
Menstrual period hormones can make you cranky, ovulation also cause mood swings due to hormonal changes, just be unlucky, your body is holding you back.
But official crime data shows women have a high ability to control their emotions and don’t use emotional issues as excuses.
It is not just blood that flows out, but also the lining of the uterus.
After menstruation, the endometrium is thinnest. Then it will gradually become thicker. The uterus is like a house. Every month, the endometrium thickens to prepare for the arrival of a “guest” (a baby). If the guest doesn't come, the endometrium is removed and rebuilt next month.
Menstruation is very inconvenient, for decades, every month for a few days bleeding 24 hours, and abdominal pain and backache, who would like to be in my shoes?
But people can be born because his mother had menstruation. Menstruation is to prepare for the 10-month house when you come to this world. Everyone should be grateful to their mothers for having regular menstruation.
Many things for women have been suppressed, society brainwashed women to be dirty, shameful, everyone thought that's the way it was, but times change.
If anyone thinks that menstruation is disgusting, that a woman's body is disgusting for preparing to nurture life, they should be ashamed to say so in public. Girls, stand up and never think that way again. Men who have never experienced it or know very little about it should be ashamed of their attitude. How can they face their mothers with that attitude? How can they want children?
Lastly, ladies, try a tampon. It really works!
