Is my foot bath leaking electricity?
Choosing the right foot bath can play a good role in foot massage and health care. Today, Gome editor will give you some suggestions on this issue.
As people's health awareness increases, foot bath tubs are more and more popular with consumers. There are a large number of different grades of foot bath tubs on the market, from over 100 yuan to over 1000 yuan, which gives consumers a lot of choices.
According to data, health care products such as foot baths are selling well compared with traditional household appliances, but there is no special industry standard for foot baths, which leads to potential safety hazards.
Mr. Li told the reporter that he had bought his father a foot bath for his birthday, but his father's feet went numb when he soaked them in it.
Mr. Li thought it was the vibration function of the foot bath that caused this, but when the vibration was turned off, my father still felt tingling in his feet.
Mr. Li tested with his stylus, which lit up. Mr. Li was surprised to find that the water in the foot bath was electrified.
Later he contacted the business, which was accommodating, but Mr. Li remained displeased.
Because he found that there were no clear industry standards for the long-popular foot tubs in terms of maximum temperature settings, target audiences, and safe materials.
But in general, electric foot baths are not a problem, though there are a few that were not properly tested before leaving the factory.
Therefore, when purchasing, choose a split type foot bath.
Separation of water and electricity, no safety hazard.
And you can measure with a stylus.
The 13th Provincial Tea Expo opens
Hunan Daily Dec.10, 2017 (Reporter Zhang Shangwu, Hu Panpan, correspondent Liu Xiaoling, photographer Li Jian) The 13th Hunan Tea Industry Expo and Xinhua black tea promotion meeting were held this morning in Hunan International Convention and Exhibition Center to display tea industry, innovate tea technology, carry forward tea culture, and accelerate the goal of tea industry reaching 10 billion yuan.
Shunli Hou, vice director of the council of China National Cooperative Federation, and Hongzhuan Ye, deputy director of the Standing Committee of the Provincial People's Congress, attended the opening ceremony.
At the opening ceremony, Professor Zhonghua Liu, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said that the origin of lake red tea is in Xinhua County.
In recent years, Hunan provincial Party committee and government have supported the development of tea industry and promoted the construction of a 100-billion-yuan tea industry, creating a colorful tea development pattern.
Black tea is getting popular again.
Provincial tea experts said that after picking green tea, black tea and dark tea can be picked. Tea farmers have income throughout the year and the output value of tea gardens is rising steadily.
At the opening ceremony, provincial leaders awarded the fourth batch of enterprises authorized to use the "Hunan black tea" trademark, and Xinhua was honored to be the origin of lake red tea.
At the newhua tea expo, a fujian tea merchant orders a kilo of “binglichun” high mountain tea.
Newly-made black tea in Hunan Province is popular and traded actively, injecting new vitality into the local tea industry.
