Zilin Ding: To a friend.
I would like to express my heartfelt gratitude for the humanitarian assistance rendered by all of you over the past 30 long years since our beloved one has passed away, especially since I personally appealed to friends at home and abroad for such assistance in early 1994.
The parents of most of the victims are now dead, and their children grown up and married.
It is your generosity that has helped us through these very difficult times.
With the COVID-19 pandemic raging around the world, most donors are retired.
I earnestly request you to stop the donation of "humanitarian donations" to us, which should have ended long ago.
I will always remember your kindness and I am sure that history will remember your act.
For various reasons I can only express my wishes in this way, please understand!
Please accept my sincere blessing.
Apple Daily photo: Tiananmen Mothers website managed by Tao Ye. pic.twitter.com/UxID9ZG
Relief funds often fail to reach the victims in time.
Since 2018, support has been provided by the Research Foundation for Corrective Studies.
Until last year, 31 years later, survivors of the June 4th massacre finally received a sum of money from Hong Kong that had been raised in the name of the victims.
We understand that Mr Ding has stopped the 64 donations, for the sake of the donors, who are all retired people and not as well off as they were before they retired. We thank him for his letter to a friend.
A special thanks and recognition to all of our friends who have been so generous and so risk a portion of their own income to send humanitarian aid.
