Today we look at some oddity hot searches.
What is normal public opinion?
Random three hot searches: February 2 Dragon Head, Price increase of good friends, and Cargo Express events. Public opinion spreads to form peaks, then decline, and finally disperse. If secondary public opinion occurs, there will be another small hump.
They look just like the model of network public opinion evolution once displayed on the website of Cyberspace Administration of China.
What is abnormal public opinion?
Six hot searches are randomly selected from the same event, presenting "solitary peak", "sawtooth" and "cliff".
In Fig. 9, the peak of one event happens to be the trough of another event, with exact timing. It must be that a unified group of water army received the task and started a new offensive.
The professionalism of black public relations is evident: dozens of hot searches are listed at the same time, which attract attention, which are responsible for popular science, which cause war and create momentum, which divert attention, which affect cognition, which mislead judgment, which incite emotions, which carry decision-making, black production accounts operate in batches and nodes, almost considering all elements of public opinion dissemination and diffusion.
Communication is a science. Without any subjective factors such as positions and emotions, just from objective data, even the black public relations will have nowhere to hide.
All things that we go through will leave traces, let's dig them out together.
Data source: hot search time machine.
