Is it reliable to buy insurance with Umbrella Insurance?
Little Umbrella is an Internet-based insurance brokerage platform.
These three requirements are actually very strict. In summary, the insurance company should have strength and be approved by the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission (CBIRC), the national authority department for supervising insurance companies and banks. The shareholders should have good conduct. As an insurance brokerage company, Umbrella Insurance doesn't need to question whether it is regular or not. After all, no insurance company can meet these three requirements.
On this point, he is reliable.
From the perspective of insurance products, Little Umbrella Insurance is an insurance supermarket where many companies' star critical illness insurances are sold. For example, the latest andsuper maria 5 critical illness insurance is sold on this platform. Both the claimant and the insurer are Ande Life Insurance, and Little Umbrella Insurance is just a third-party intermediary. Its reliability is not in doubt.
In terms of payment mode: Internet platform products, because less the operating expenses of business outlets and the cost of business staff, so Internet products generally have high cost performance, and flexible payment methods, support monthly payment, reduce the payment pressure of policyholders, at the same time can maximize the leverage of insurance.
That's very good.
Sure, please let me know.
from the business perspective: this is particularly important, because insurance is a highly professional industry. Many internet products allow customers to insure themselves, which leads to many misunderstandings. In terms of health and occupation, non-insurance practitioners often add their own subjective opinions when applying for insurance, thinking that they are healthy or meet the requirements. This can lead to many claims risks and the possibility of being denied.
I used to do insurance telemarketing for Tencent Microinsurance, which is the same as Umbrella, an internet insurance brokerage platform.
Internet insurance is reliable, what's not reliable are people. Internet channels don't have professional practitioners, and there are a lot of sales misdirection.
These marketing strategies are not wrong, but they avoid the important information and don't tell policyholders that the first month is 1 yuan, but the next month is charged according to normal rate, which ranges from dozens to 200 yuan. Many customers don't know what they have bought after paying for one or two years.
I thought I could spend 1 yuan and the insurance company would pay 6 million yuan.
Free mobile phone is only for special policy numbers such as 6666, 8888. And if you win the prize and don't exchange it, no one will remind you.
This is another pitfall for policy holders. They can get a free coverage of 60,000 yuan for critical illness insurance, but it's short-term. If they only have this and no other commercial insurance, once the critical illness happens, the 60,000 yuan will not be enough to solve their problems, and they will start running naked in life.
Currently, there are strict crackdowns on mislead of internet insurance sales.
So, in conclusion, the platform is not the problem and neither is the product. It's the salesperson's professionalism and ethics that matter.
I suggest that you consider all options carefully. Offline insurance brokers offer a wider range of products and more choices for customers. Some products are better value than those offered online.
I have helped 59 Internet customers to underwrite offline products, which can save 2000-3000 yuan per person per year.
Feel free to communicate with me if you have any questions.
I am the agent of Mingya, with 3 years of experience in corporate management training. I have served nearly a thousand enterprise users and cooperated with more than 100 insurance companies. Before insuring, I will customize insurance products for customers according to their needs. During the insurance process, I will shop around for customers and try my best to get the best underwriting results for them. After insuring, I will organize and manage insurance policies for customers, so that customers can feel at ease.
Lifelong learning with every client.
I hope my answer can help the question owner!
According to the definition of China Insurance Regulatory Commission, Internet insurance refers to the insurance business that can be independently completed by policyholders after clicking the insurance application links.
There is no need for the policy owner to sign or for the insurance adviser to sign at any point in this process. The policy owner can do it all themselves.
Although there is no special “insurance application ceremony” for internet insurance, and there may not even be a printed contract, it doesn’t mean that the electronic contract is invalid or has no legal effect.
This is a bit like a “telemarketing” assembly line, but there is a fatal problem with buying insurance this way: the follow-up service may not keep up.
Insurance is usually a long-term contract for decades. When we buy insurance, should we seriously consider whether the agent we choose is one who can accompany us for a long time and provide us with services many years later?
