Meta is essentially an advertising company. Ad companies make money today by having their own traffic channels.
Facebook, Instagram, Whatsapp etc. Whatever the feature, they are all Meta's traffic channels.
In addition, Meta is the largest advertising alliance. Many apps connect Meta's advertising and monetize through Meta's advertising platform.
But times have changed.
First, Meta has difficulty to get user data due to Apple's privacy policy adjustment, which affects the efficiency of advertising placement.
Apple's current privacy policy is very user-friendly. It clearly tells users what information an app can access and most people will say no.
Google's next move will have a bigger impact on Meta's revenue.
Second, the contribution of China to Meta’s revenue growth has diminished (the exact share is not known but it was there).
It is not accurate that Meta has no business in China.
Meta gets at least 10% of its revenue from China, mainly from Chinese companies that go global.
Meta has a few hundred people in Hong Kong and many agents in mainland China.
Chinese companies trying to go global, but Meta owns the ad channels and gets most of the money.
It's interesting that ByteDance’s TikTok is now one of Meta’s main competitors, but Meta made a lot of money from ByteDance two years ago.
All domestic agents are helping ByteDance to place ads with Meta, and Meta Greater China has also achieved good performance.
I haven't checked it out lately, but it can't be any better than before.
The era of Chinese companies spending big money overseas is over.
Third, new traffic channels are not expanding well.
Facebook is getting older and the new platforms including TikTok are not in Meta's hands.
The biggest problem is not just the fall in income, but the lack of growth expectations.
Capital market doesn't only focus on income, but also on future expectation.
Meta's expectations are apparently not enough.
To tell a new story to the market, Zuckerberg talked about the “metaverse”.
The metaverse is indeed one of the future directions, but the realization cycle of the metaverse is relatively long. This story should not be enough to support Meta's market value in the next two or three years.
So the next two years should be tough for Meta.
Although Facebook is doing very well and earning $100 billion to $200 billion a year, it has no safety moat compared with other Internet companies and high-tech companies.
Although his several social media apps still have high daily active users and are mainstream social media platforms, such as Facebook, WhatsApp, etc., Facebook is not confident in the face of the rapid development of TikTok. Disruption can happen in an instant.
The reason that Facebook is in such danger is because they are trying to do the elusive thing that no one has ever succeeded at doing, and they are failing miserably. That's why Zuckerberg keeps changing the company name and looking for new things to do. I think he is wrong.
Those who have obtained the first-level or second-level registered fire engineer qualification certificates can practice in the name of registered fire engineers at corresponding levels.
The fire departments of the public security organs at the provincial, autonomous region and municipal levels are the registration authorities for Level II registered fire engineers, and are responsible for the preliminary examination of Level I registered fire engineers.
For applications that are accepted or rejected, written vouchers shall be issued with the special seal of the fire department of the public security organ at this level and the date.
The certificate is the practicing certificate of registered fire engineers at corresponding levels, which are kept and used by themselves.
When applying for initial registration after the due date, the continuing education requirements of these regulations shall be met.
The specific measures for the registration administration, such as initial registration, renewal registration, change registration, cancellation registration and non-registration shall be separately stipulated by the Ministry of Public Security.
During each registration period, registered fire engineers at all levels shall complete the required continuing education.
That's all for today's exam information sharing. Hope this helps.
